snippet.title: Apple hires Yves Saint Laurent CEO Paul Deneve
snippet.description: With a nod to the luxury fashion world, the tech giant brings former YSL CEO on board to work on "special projects."

snippet.title: The value of things: a great hi-fi vs. a $23,000 Yves Saint Laurent sweater
snippet.description: Luxury markets are booming and the Audiophiliac wonders why the high-end audio industry isn't getting its fair share of the glory.

snippet.title: Google Santa Tracker follows Saint Nick around the world
snippet.description: You can keep tabs on Father Christmas using not just one, but two Santa trackers. Better get the mince pies ready.

snippet.title: August smart lock, from Yves Behar, to ship in Q1 2014
snippet.description: The company began taking preorders today and also announced a new feature that locks a door automatically every time it is closed.

snippet.title: Facebook boots up Mobile Games Publishing
snippet.description: The company will act as a publisher for small- and mid-sized game developers, helping them get their creations out to more people.

snippet.title: Ubuntu Edge dual-boots Android, seeks $32M
snippet.description: The Ubuntu Edge runs both Android and open-source Ubuntu Touch software -- and the people behind it want your help to the tune of $32 million on Indiegogo.

snippet.title: Jetman Yves Rossy flies in formation with jet squad
snippet.description: Anyone glancing up at the skies over the Swiss Alps recently might have been suprised to see a bloke flying alongside some fighter jets.

snippet.title: Is it a problem if Windows 8 boots too quickly?
snippet.description: Microsoft's forthcoming operating system boots so quickly that you will miss those familiar prompts.

snippet.title: Saint Gobain invests in self-tinting 'smart glass'
snippet.description: Building materials company pays $80 million for stake in Sage Electrochromics and plans to build a large-scale factory to make energy-saving glass.

snippet.title: What to do when a Mac always boots to verbose or single-user modes
snippet.description: Apple supplies various alternate boot modes for OS X, but sometimes systems get stuck in them.
